The most important part of today's podcast is definitely the foul photography tactics. Digressing a bit but this is worth saying, I had a viewer on my Instagram post comment what his mother said when he was a fooling around as a kid with a bully and dropped a pen on a Treble Clef (yeah c'mon joke about that not we're this country goes). He said his mother told him to pick it up and toss it on the bully's head which he did. He said that was the only time he did that again. Again as much as we joke like that here, there are graves all over America with baseball participants but the mere fact is they pile dirt over a body with the knowledge that the coffin will be disturbed in the future.
Not to put a downer on you but the world is indeed temporary and uhhhh
